SIMPLE: parietal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parietal
<hw>Pa*ri"e*tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>parietalis</ets>, fr. <ets>paries</ets>, <ets>-ietis</ets>, a wall:
cf. F. <ets>pari⟦eacute⟧tal</ets>. Cf. <er>Parietary</er>,
<er>Pellitory</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a wall; hence, pertaining to
buildings or the care of them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resident within the walls or buildings of a
college.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At Harvard College, the officers resident within the college walls
constitute a permanent standing committee, called the
<qex>Parietal</qex> Committee.</q> <rj><qau>B. H. Hall
(1856).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to
the parietes.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of, pertaining to, or in the
region of, the parietal bones, which form the upper and middle part of
the cranium, between the frontals and occipitals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Attached to the main wall of the
ovary, and not to the axis; -- said of a placenta.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parietal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Parietal
<hw>Pa*ri"e*tal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>One of the parietal bones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the special scales, or
plates, covering the back of the head in certain reptiles and
fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parietary</ent>⟦br⟧
